params.hints:
Use SELECT * only if you need all columns from table
LIMIT without ORDER BY causes non-deterministic results, depending on the query execution plan

statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from (select '1' as row_count from `videos` inner join `languages` on `languages`.`id` = `videos`.`language_id` inner join `video_albums` on `video_albums`.`id` = `videos`.`video_album_id` where `videos`.`video_album_id` > '0' order by `videos`.`position` asc) count_row_table

select count(*) as aggregate from (select '1' as row_count from `videos` inner join `languages` on `languages`.`id` = `videos`.`language_id` inner join `video_albums` on `video_albums`.`id` = `videos`.`video_album_id` where `videos`.`video_album_id` > '0' order by `videos`.`position` asc) count_row_table

select `videos`.`id`, 0 as albumid, `videos`.`name`, `video_albums`.`name` as `category`, `videos`.`album_cover`, `languages`.`name` as `language`, `videos`.`created_at` from `videos` inner join `languages` on `languages`.`id` = `videos`.`language_id` inner join `video_albums` on `video_albums`.`id` = `videos`.`video_album_id` where `videos`.`video_album_id` > '0' order by `videos`.`position` asc, `videos`.`id` asc limit 10 offset 0
